<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by ElBigmac on 07-19-2001 11:49 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Everyone agrees (or should agree) that Verant did the right thing when they banned all the cheaters. Its not called a cheat for nothing.

But, the reason why Smed is made an ass of himself by starting this thread is because he asked people who can only enjoy this game by cheating to stop so they dont have to ban them and they still get the 10$ a month from them.

This means "We dont really want you around, but we like money so just stop whatever your doing, even tough it means the game will suck for you now, and keep on giving us the monthly fee please."

What a lame thing to ask. This alone is a small insult. The bigger insult is poeple will do it. They will give Verant their money and play the game till they cant stand it anymore and decide to cheat again and maybe get banned or dump the game.

"The truth is once I was banned, I realized how much time I spent on that damned game, and how much fun I actually got from it."

You used the game, and cheated and had fun. Dont get me wrong, but I doubt very much you will still have fun playing this game the way Verant made it.

"Secondly, people that bitch at Smed and Verant don't seem to realize how stupid they sound. Verant created EverQuest. If you don't like the game, don't play. If you play the game, you must get *some* form of fun from it, or you wouldn't play. Therefore, if your 'enemies' didn't exist or were shut down, you'd lose the game you get fun from."

Again, EQ has massive content and great playability... But the game mechanics make it too damned SLOW AND BORING. That alone will satisfie many people, but some need someting different. You see this massive game and realize how much fun it could be till you try it and realise its sooOOOO SLOOOOWW. You then have a choice... you can stop playing, as many do including me, or you can cheat and make it fun to play, even for you.

To many people, the game was fun BECAUSE they could cheat. I guess it all depends on personal taste. There will always be cheaters because of that.</TEXTAREA>
